    <div class="policy-section reveal">
      <h2>Stainless Steel Frames</h2>
      <p>Our frames are crafted from brushed stainless steel — a material chosen for its durability and resistance to tarnish. With a little routine care, it will retain its appearance for decades.</p>
      <h3>Routine Cleaning</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Wipe down with a clean, dry microfibre cloth to remove everyday dust and fingerprints.</li>
        <li>For marks that won't lift dry, dampen the cloth lightly with water and wipe in the direction of the grain.</li>
        <li>A small amount of mild, pH-neutral washing-up liquid on a damp cloth is safe for more persistent residue.</li>
        <li>Always dry immediately after any wet wipe — do not leave moisture on the frame.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>What to Avoid</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Abrasive pads, scourers, or steel wool — these will permanently scratch the brushed finish.</li>
        <li>Bleach, chlorine-based products, or undiluted household cleaners.</li>
        <li>Solvent-based sprays such as WD-40, acetone, or nail varnish remover.</li>
        <li>Leaving salt water, hairspray, or perfume on the surface — rinse away promptly if contact occurs.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section reveal">
      <h2>Mirror Glass</h2>
      <p>All MUNLER mirrors use ecological, silvering-free mirror glass. The reflective layer sits closer to the surface than conventional mirrors, so cleaning with the right products preserves its clarity and longevity.</p>
      <h3>Routine Cleaning</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Use a specialist glass cleaner or a 50/50 solution of distilled white vinegar and water, applied to a microfibre cloth — not directly onto the glass.</li>
        <li>Buff in circular motions with a dry lint-free cloth to finish without streaks.</li>
        <li>For light dust, a dry microfibre cloth is usually sufficient.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>What to Avoid</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Ammonia-based glass cleaners (many commercial window sprays contain ammonia) — these degrade the mirror coating over time.</li>
        <li>Spraying liquids directly onto the mirror surface — moisture can seep behind the glass and cause edge silvering damage.</li>
        <li>Rough or abrasive cloths, paper towels, or newspaper.</li>
        <li>Excessive pressure on the glass, particularly near the frame edge.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section reveal">
      <h2>Furniture Surfaces</h2>
      <p>Our end tables and furniture pieces combine stainless steel with stone or powder-coated surfaces depending on the product. Follow the guidance below for each material.</p>
      <h3>Stone Tops</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Wipe spills immediately — stone is porous and can stain if liquid is left sitting.</li>
        <li>Use a damp cloth with a small amount of neutral soap for routine cleaning.</li>
        <li>Do not use acidic cleaners (lemon, vinegar) on stone — they can etch the surface.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Powder-Coated Surfaces</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Clean with a damp cloth and mild detergent only.</li>
        <li>Avoid solvents, which can lift the coating.</li>
        <li>Do not place very hot items directly onto powder-coated surfaces.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section reveal">
      <h2>Placement &amp; Environment</h2>
      <p>Where you place your MUNLER piece is as important as how you clean it. The right environment will preserve both function and appearance.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Avoid prolonged direct sunlight.</strong> UV exposure can cause discolouration over time, particularly on mirror glass and upholstered elements.</li>
        <li><strong>Keep away from high humidity.</strong> Bathrooms without proper ventilation, or rooms with consistently high moisture, can accelerate edge oxidation on mirror glass. Ensure adequate airflow.</li>
        <li><strong>Maintain clearance from heat sources.</strong> Radiators, fireplaces, and underfloor heating vents can cause thermal stress on glass and affect adhesive behind the mirror.</li>
        <li><strong>Secure wall fixings.</strong> Always hang mirrors using the supplied fixings or appropriate wall anchors rated for the weight. Never hang on a single nail or adhesive strip alone.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-section reveal">
      <h2>Long-Term Maintenance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Inspect wall fixings annually — vibration from nearby doors or windows can gradually loosen fixings over time.</li>
        <li>If the frame develops a surface mark from light impact, a specialist stainless steel restorer (applied with the grain) can often minimise the appearance.</li>
        <li>Contact us before attempting any remedial work — we may be able to advise or assist.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Your piece is covered by our 5-Year Warranty against manufacturing defects. For full details, visit the <a href="/pages/warranty">Warranty page</a>.</p>
    </div>

